cadMplsMIB.name: cadMplsMIB

revisions.description: Changed min value for cadMplsLdpHelloHoldTimer and cadMplsLdpTargetedHelloHoldTimer from 0 to 1

cadMplsMIB.contactinfo: Arris Technical Support Postal: ARRIS E-Mail: support@arrisi.com
cadMplsMIB.description: This is the management MIB contains Cadant proprietary MPLS MIB information. Copyright 2013 Arris International, Inc. All rights reserved.

cadMplsLdpHelloHoldTimer.name: cadMplsLdpHelloHoldTimer
cadMplsLdpHelloHoldTimer.description: The 16-bit integer value which is the configured link Hello hold timer for the local LDP router in seconds. A value of 65535 means infinite

cadMplsLdpTargetedHelloHoldTimer.name: cadMplsLdpTargetedHelloHoldTimer
cadMplsLdpTargetedHelloHoldTimer.description: The 16-bit integer value which is the configured targeted Hello hold timer for the local LDP router in seconds. A value of 65535 means infinite

cadMplsLdpKeepAliveHoldTimer.name: cadMplsLdpKeepAliveHoldTimer
cadMplsLdpKeepAliveHoldTimer.description: The 16-bit integer value which is the configured Keep Alive hold timer for the local LDP router in seconds.

cadMplsLdpVcDescription.name: cadMplsLdpVcDescription
cadMplsLdpVcDescription.description: This is the 64 byte string configured as an LDP Interface Parameter PW Description.

cadMplsLdpNeighborAddressType.name: cadMplsLdpNeighborAddressType
cadMplsLdpNeighborAddressType.description: This is the MPLS Peer Address Type. Only ipv4(1) or ipv6(2) will be supported.

cadMplsLdpNeighborIpAddress.name: cadMplsLdpNeighborIpAddress
cadMplsLdpNeighborIpAddress.description: This is the IP address of the LDP neighbor. IPv4 and IPv6 addresses are supported.

cadMplsLdpNeighborPassword.name: cadMplsLdpNeighborPassword
cadMplsLdpNeighborPassword.description: This is the MD5 password used for TCP authentication for this LDP neighbor.

cadMplsLdpNeighborTargetedPeer.name: cadMplsLdpNeighborTargetedPeer
cadMplsLdpNeighborTargetedPeer.description: If this value is set to true, then this neighbor is a CLI configured Targeted LDP peer. The CMTS will consider this peer eligible so will accept discovery messages from it and will actively try to establish a T-LDP session with the peer. If this value is set to false then this neighbor is a regular link LDP neighbor and a row in this table will be used for storing the password only.

cadMplsLdpNeighborRowStatus.name: cadMplsLdpNeighborRowStatus
cadMplsLdpNeighborRowStatus.description: Row Status for this table entry.
